handist.collections.dist

Class DistBag<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • handist.collections.Bag<T>
      • handist.collections.dist.DistBag<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the elements handled by the DistBag.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    apgas.util.SerializableWithReplace, com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, DistributedCollection<T,DistBag<T>>, ParallelReceiver<T>, Serializable, Iterable<T>

    public class DistBag<T>
extends Bag<T>
implements DistributedCollection<T,DistBag<T>>, apgas.util.SerializableWithReplace
    A class for handling objects at multiple places. It is allowed to add new elements dynamically. This class provides methods for load balancing.

    Note: In its current implementation, there are some limitations.

    • There is only one load balancing method
    • The method flattens the number of elements of the all places
    See Also:

      • moveAtSyncCount

        public void moveAtSyncCount(int count,
                            apgas.Place destination,
                            MoveManager mm)
        Removes the specified number of entries from the local Bag and prepares them to be transfered to the specified place when the CollectiveMoveManager.sync() method of the CollectiveMoveManager is called.

        The objects are not removed from the local collection until method CollectiveMoveManager.sync() is called. If the destination is the local placce, this method has no effects.

        Parameters:
        count - number of objects to move from this instance
        destination - the destination of the objects
        mm - move manager in charge of making the transfer

      • writeReplace

        public Object writeReplace()
                    throws ObjectStreamException
        Description copied from interface: DistributedCollection
        Method used to create an object which will be transferred to a remote place.

        This method is present in interface DistributedCollection to force the implementation in implementing classes. Implementation should return a LazyObjectReference instance capable of initializing the local handle of the implementing class on the remote place

        Specified by:
